    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-05-29T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-05-29T11:00:00-05:00" n="349"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d349">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 658.119/399</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LIB1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Laughlin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-05-29T17:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 29, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 8.22 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>10324. War Trade Board [from <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1"
                        >Sheldon</persName>]:</p>
                <p>No. 675. The Swedish agreement was signed this afternoon subject to ratification
                    which Swedish delegates state is only matter of form as their Government has not
                        [<hi rend="italic">now?</hi>] seen full text. Will cable you a summary of
                    some of the important changes in the draft agreement which was sent you on May
                    21, as well as summary of covering letters exchanged. Do not publish contents
                    until further advised but no harm in announcing that agreement has been signed.
                    Please notify Shipping Board.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LIB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Laughlin</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
